# Frontend Design System — Soulspedia

## Design Vocabulary
Soulspedia is a **lore archive**, not a game fan site. Every design decision should feel like an ancient tome, a museum exhibit, or an academic journal — rendered in dark fantasy.

Keywords: **solemn · weighty · cinematic · atmospheric · scholarly**
Anti-keywords: bouncy · playful · bright · rounded · generic

---

## Visual Hierarchy

```tsx
// H1 — Page titles, hero headings
<h1 className="font-optimus uppercase tracking-[0.08em] text-5xl md:text-7xl text-amber-100/90">
  Dark Souls
</h1>

// H2 — Section titles
<h2 className="font-optimus uppercase tracking-[0.06em] text-2xl md:text-3xl text-white/82">
  The Lords of Cinder
</h2>

// H3 — Card titles, subsections
<h3 className="font-optimus uppercase tracking-[0.06em] text-sm text-amber-100/80">
  Artorias
</h3>

// Lore body text
<p className="font-lore text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-[#e0e0d8] tracking-tight">
  In the Age of Fire...
</p>

// Subtitle / descriptor
<p className="font-lore text-sm text-white/40 tracking-tight">
  Knight of Gwyn · Lord of Cinder
</p>
```

